As an added bonus, its just a short run away from Ak'anon, everytime the castle mobs decided to take a stroll around the zone(you wouldnt believe what kind of train a bard can produce...), i gated home, sold my loot and went back.<br>
After i soloed there for a while, i got tells from every group in the zone that wanted me to join, one even kicked out a rogue to make room for me(poor dwarf, i didnt want that)<br>
I think Jobekn made a good impression on them soloing the light blue and green mobs without trouble, i was proud of him.I think i made a yellow bubble and ~150 plat for 2 hours hunting, would have been better if i had soloed and the tanks hadnt looted all the FS, but i am a lazy mage.<br>
And i could amaze the group with my powerful summonings, those elves had no idea what a dimensional hole is. I really enjoyed all the &quot;Oooohs&quot; and &quot;Aaahs&quot;.<br>
It was a very nice experience, and i believe that there will be a lot of /shouts &quot;Group looking for a magician&quot; in MM for some time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Just remember to use an Air pet and malise casters when you solo, they burn you down real fast when they start chaincasting on you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(5/6/02 11:30:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Loot and Exp</span><hr size=1> well, Thurgadin Mines can be good and bad ;-)<br>
<br>
It is a pretty nice spot, but also on my server (SolRo) it's sometimes pretty overcamped. well, not really overcamped, but one of those lvl 50+ people in there is enough of not leaving anything for you to kill.<br>
<br>
Happens unfortunately pretty often.<br>
<br>
As for the heads, either people on SolRo are very avaricious or they don't need those heads (anymore ,-) ).<br>
Once I as able to sell my first 2 heads for 50pp each, but now I'm carrying 6 heads with me nobody wants to buy. Once somebody offered 25pp for one, but I didn't want to sell for that price ;-)<br>
And I already gave up hope to sell them for 100 or 75pp, meanwhile I think I were happy if I could find a buyer for 50pp per head again ;-)<br>
<br>
But beside that...when you are there and can't get into Thurgadin Mines I think GD is a very crappy place for xp especially.<br>
Either there is an extreme xp penalty in this zone (does something like that exist?) or I don't know what's going wrong.<br>
was a few times in groups which killed Giants (4-6 players of lvl 31-36) and we almost killed them non-stop, but after 2 or 3 hours I had just gotten slightly more than 1 blue (!) bubble.<br>
same for the Tizmacks. was there yesterday together with 1 druid lvl 35 and later with another druid lvl 36 and after probably 20-30 Tizmacks I had maybe gotten 1 blue bubble of xp.<br>
<br>
Thuradin MInes are nice, but hard to access (and I never have seen more reckless high lvl people than there, nobody cares if you are sitting infront of a spawn point (like at the water). when they see the MOBs pop they kill them. And if you happen to get a reply to your question &quot;why are you killing them...?&quot; you usually get an answer like &quot;I'm bored&quot; or &quot;I don't really reckognize any camps, whoever kills them first gets them&quot; and more of this.<br>
They aren't getting a single point of xp for them probably but still I've seen nobody carying about the fact that there is sitting somebody who gets xp for them.<br>
I even have seen it a few times that I just pulled one witha  Nuke but the high lvl guys just came to where I was fighting the MOB and easily did more than 50%  dmg. There's nothing a lvl 35 Mage can do about it if there's somebody who kills them with 1 Nuke (or at least does over 50% damage with one)<br>
<br>
Oh my...pretty frustrating ;-) <p><img SRC="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_zdd2.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(5/8/02 9:38:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Loot and Exp</span><hr size=1> Ok it won't help the author of the thread anymore I guess, but maybe somebody else needs it at a later time.<br>
Yesterday I went from Thurgadin to Rathe Mountains to kill Cynthia.<br>
<br>
you can read more about that in the threads about her, so I will make it short:<br>
- xp is somewhat ok. (at least for me personally it is faster than in Thurgadin Mines, especially because I died a few times in there, which costs of course always a lot of time)<br>
- loot: if you get a few Coldain heads in Thurgadin Mines AND are able to sell them for 50-100pp then Thurgadin Mines is definately better. But Cynthia drops up to 5p in coins and also items which can be sold for up to 6pp. I think in 4 hours there I made at least 150pp yesterday, which is pretty nice for me. (maybe even more, so far I have 100pp in my pockets from her, and estimated the value of the items I havent sold yet to about 50pp, but it might be more) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showPrevMessage?topicID=26.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showNextMessage?topicID=26.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.threadControl?topicID=26.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstow